If the ſtomach ſtill refuſes the bark in the above ways, try it in triple quantities in clyſters, or try the vinous tincture, No. 4. The bark is the only chance, we are therefore to perſiſt in its uſe till a cure is made. Three drops of oil of vitriol in a glaſs of water every hour, may be tryed where the delicacy of the ſtomach or fever, will not admit any preparation of bark; 
                           〈◊〉
                         as it is apt to gripe, it ſhould never be uſed when the bowels are affected.
